<p>&amp; does not seem to lose an opportunity of letting loose at our Col. who takes it all smiling.<br/>Yesterday afternoon one of the Staff captains came bustling up, on our arrival, &amp; quite excitedly <strike>informed</strike> pointed out a flag marked pitch as our ground on which to bivouac.<br/>"Yes" answered the Colonel "are'nt they pretty flags?"<br/>We left Blandford at 6.30 this morning &amp; are now a further nine miles on our way.  We reached here at midday &amp; stay the night in a fine&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    hilly paddock</p>
